// Phase 3c slice test — popCount on [32]. Copied verbatim from
// exercises/functional-correctness/popcount/Popcount.cry. The
// interesting Cryptol shape is the self-referential comprehension
// (ic = [0] # [ ... | ... <- ic ]). Whether this fully specializes
// to a concrete tape of bvAdds — i.e. whether scNormalize unrolls
// the 32-element fold — is what this test pins. If translation
// fails, the diagnostic surfaces the unmapped primitive (typically
// a Cryptol-prelude ec* form) and we know what to add next.

write_lean_cryptol_module
  "Popcount.cry"
  "test_cryptol_module_popcount.module.lean" [] [];
